Class CNumberFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.motor.CNumberFactory

  • public class CNumberFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a numeric value-type, defined via a primitive Java Number type and specific numeric range.

      • range

        public static CNumber range(INumber min,
                            INumber max)
        Creates a numeric value-type with the specified limits. The number-type will be derived from the specified limit-values, which must have identical number-types, or one of which must represent an infinite value, and hence will not have a specific number-type. If both limits represent infinite values then an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        min - Minimnum value for value-type
        max - Maximnum value for value-type
        Returns:
        Created value-type
        Throws:
        KModelException - if minimnum value is greater than maximnum value, or if minimnum and maximnum values have incompatible number-types

      • range
